TYPESCRIPT
- Zero `any`. Every MDX frontmatter field, API route handler,
  form state, and utility function is fully typed.
- Use zod for ALL runtime validation: frontmatter parsing,
  contact form input, API response shapes.

SERVER VS CLIENT
- app/blog/page.tsx           → RSC
- app/blog/[slug]/page.tsx    → RSC
- BlogSection on homepage     → RSC (reads files at build time)
- Contact form UI             → 'use client' (form state, fetch)
- Contact API route           → server (Next.js Route Handler)
- Testimonials section        → RSC (static data from data file)

MDX RENDERING
- Use next-mdx-remote/rsc for RSC-compatible MDX rendering.
  Do NOT use @next/mdx (requires webpack config changes and
  does not support dynamic routes cleanly).
- Use gray-matter for frontmatter parsing from .mdx files.
- Custom MDX components for every HTML element that needs
  styling — never leave unstyled prose on the page.

FORM HANDLING
- No form libraries (no react-hook-form, no formik).
  Plain React state + fetch. Keep it simple and dependency-free.
- Zod validates on BOTH client (before submit) and server
  (in the API route). Never trust client-only validation.
- Nodemailer with Gmail SMTP for email delivery.
  Uses the developer's own Gmail account as sender.
  Requires a Gmail App Password (not the account password).
  No third-party email service account needed.

