──── 1C. FILE SYSTEM HELPERS ──────────────────────────────

Still in lib/mdx.ts — implement these four functions:

  POSTS_DIR = path.join(process.cwd(), 'content/blog')

  export function getPostSlugs(): string[]
    Read filenames from POSTS_DIR with fs.readdirSync.
    Filter: only .mdx files.
    Return filenames without extension.
    If POSTS_DIR does not exist: return [].

  export function getPostBySlug(slug: string): Post | null
    Read file: path.join(POSTS_DIR, `${slug}.mdx`)
    If file doesn't exist: return null.
    Parse with gray-matter.
    Validate frontmatter with frontmatterSchema.safeParse.
    If validation fails: log a warning and return null
      (never crash the build over a malformed post).
    Calculate readingTime with readingTime(content).text.
    Return the full Post object.

  export function getAllPosts(): PostMeta[]
    Call getPostSlugs(), map to getPostBySlug().
    Filter nulls. Filter published: false posts.
    Strip the content field (return PostMeta only).
    Sort: newest first by date (descending).

  export function getFeaturedPosts(): PostMeta[]
    getAllPosts().filter(p => p.featured)
    If no featured posts: return first 3 from getAllPosts().

  export function getRelatedPosts(
    slug: string,
    tags: string[]
  ): PostMeta[]
    Get all posts excluding the current slug.
    Score each post by number of matching tags.
    Return top 3 by score (or 3 most recent if no tag overlap).

