──── 2A. HOW GMAIL SMTP WORKS FOR THIS USE CASE ───────────

Nodemailer connects directly to Gmail's SMTP server using
the developer's Gmail account credentials. The account
password is NOT used — Gmail requires an App Password, which
is a 16-character code generated in Google Account settings
specifically for apps that don't support OAuth2.

The email flow:
  Contact form submit
    → Next.js API route (/api/contact)
      → Nodemailer creates SMTP transport
        → Connects to smtp.gmail.com:587 (TLS)
          → Authenticates with Gmail App Password
            → Delivers notification email to developer
            → Delivers confirmation email to visitor
              → Returns success to form

Gmail free tier limits:
  500 emails per day (Gmail free account)
  More than sufficient for a portfolio contact form.

